Description of the Case :¶

This case is about a bank (Thera Bank) which has a growing customer base. Majority of these customers are liability customers (depositors) with varying size of deposits. The number of customers who are also borrowers (asset customers) is quite small, and the bank is interested in expanding this base rapidly to bring in more loan business and in the process, earn more through the interest on loans. In particular, the management wants to explore ways of converting its liability customers to personal loan customers (while retaining them as depositors). A campaign that the bank ran last year for liability customers showed a healthy conversion rate of over 9% success. This has encouraged the retail marketing department to devise campaigns with better target marketing to increase the success ratio with minimal budget.

The department wants to build a model that will help them identify the potential customers who have higher probability of purchasing the loan. This will increase the success ratio while at the same time reduce the cost of the campaign. The file Bank.xls contains data on 5000 customers. The data include customer demographic information (age, income, etc.), the customer's relationship with the bank (mortgage, securities account, etc.), and the customer response to the last personal loan campaign (Personal Loan). Among these 5000 customers, only 480 (= 9.6%) accepted the personal loan that was offered to them in the earlier campaign.

Input Variables:¶

  • ID:Customer ID
  • Age:Customer's age in completed years
  • Experience:#years of professional experience
  • Income:Annual income of the customer.
  • ZIPCode:Home Address ZIP code.
  • Family:Family size of the customer.
  • CCAvg:Avg. spending on credit cards per month
  • Education:Education Level. 1: Undergrad; 2: Graduate; 3: Advanced/Professional
  • Mortgage:Value of house mortgage if any.
  • Securities Account:Does the customer have a securities account with the bank?
  • CD Account:Does the customer have a certificate of deposit (CD) account with the bank?
  • Online:Does the customer use internet banking facilities?
  • CreditCard:Does the customer use a credit card issued by UniversalBank?

Target Variables:¶

  • Personal Loan:Did this customer accept the personal loan offered in the last campaign?

In [6]:
def find_boundary(df,variable,distance):
    upper_bound=df[variable].mean()+distance*df[variable].std()
    lower_bound=df[variable].mean()-distance*df[variable].std()
    return upper_bound,lower_bound

Summary:¶

  1. Decision trees has shown Higher accuracy score of 0.98 compared to that of Logistic regression i.e 0.94.
  2. As our data set is a biased towards class 0, with 90% customer in Class 0, So accuracy_score is not that much significant for validation rather F1 score can be more significant.
  3. f1-score for decision tree model is for both claas 1 and Class 0 is higher than Logistic regression model that kind of helped lot to choose decision tree over Logistic regression model.
  4. As our data set is a biased towards class 0, with 90% customer in Class 0 and less than 10% in Class 1 of Personal Loan ,so Class 0 exhibits higher recall values(True Negative Rate) than Class 1, i.e 99% of the class 0 customers are correctly predicted as compared to 84% (True Positive Rate) of the class 1 customers are predicted correctly.
  5. Class 1 has precision of 0.92, i.e 92% of the class 1 prediction are accurate which infers 92% of the customer whom our model has predicted as potential customer for poersonal Loan are actually taken the personal Loan.
  6. Decision tree model has shown error rate of 2% only as compared to 6% that of Logistic model.
  7. As we can compare Train data and Test data in perspective of ROC curve and AUC score and Decision Tree has given much better AUC score of 0.91 in Test data against AUC score of 0.99 in train set.
  8. Decision Tree algorithm is showing better accuracy, precision, recall, f1-score for both class 0 and class 1 than that of Logistic regression mode, so I'll prefer Decision tree over logistic for this problem.
  9. D

Final Summary:¶

  • Customers having higher income has opted more for personal Loan, mostly customer income with more than 100000 dollars has more choice of Personal Loan
  • Customers with age of below 26 and greater than 65 are not taking personal loan and that is quite obvious.
  • Customers with Experience more than 41 has not opted for Personal Loan and exeperience with 10 yrs has opted more personal loan
  • Customers having Higher Monthly spending towards Credit card are likely to be our potential target Customers.
